        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Experimental boundary conditions matched within 2% of CFD inlet conditions",
        "description": "Flow rate, rotational speed, and fluid viscosity used in bench experiments must be matched to CFD boundary conditions within 2% to ensure comparability."
      },
      "rationale": "FDA pump experiments were conducted at 2500 and 3500 RPM across flow rates of 2.5–6 L/min. CFD boundary conditions replicate these within 1.3% for flow rate and 0.8% for RPM. Level 3 achieved."
    },
